text.headline: Sea mist prediction.
text.text:
In collaboration with IMT ATLANTIQUE and ACTIMAR.
Building a pipeline to predict sea mist in real time using meteorological and geographical and METAR data collected from Brest airport. The aim is to add an analytical/statistical component to Actimar's expertise in this important factor for maritime navigation.

text.headline: IoT meets AI.
text.text: a 3 day summer school at Munich in collaboration with TUM and Siemens which concluded with a real time hand sign detection solution.

text.headline: Bug prediction.
text.text: Internship at Amadeus which consists in the creation of a bug prediction model that alerts the developers in case of a high probability of causing a bug. the training/ testing observations were labeled using the SZZ heuristic (state of the art in bug labeling).

text.headline: Detection of task entry anomalies in Planisware
text.text: Internship within Planisware which consists in creating an anomaly detection model regarding to task entries in Planisware software. Once the anomaly is detected (predefined threshold) it will be sent to a manager who will confirm or deny it. The aim of the project is to keep the software very permissible and free, while maintaining compliance levers.

text.headline: Churn Modeling
text.text: Project at ITM ATLANTIQUE in collaboration with HSBC France to create a model for targeting customers with a high probability of cancelling their provident insurance contract. The model used is based on Uplift models, which calculate the effectiveness of a marketing campaign or sales action for a given category of customer. The idea is to target those customers who will 'churn' and who may change their mind as a result of a sales action.

text.headline: Address extraction, normalization and enrichment.
text.text: Implementing a pipeline to extract an address from a text (number, type, street name and postal code) and the associated cadastral reference, normalize it using a geopy framework and enrich it using a database containing the cadastres with the associated addresses.

text.headline: Debtor segmentation the BNPP Personal Finance activity.
text.text: prioritization of debtor files to be contacted according to their likelihood of payment. The model made it possible to halve the number of FTEs used for this activity, while maintaining the same performance threshold.

text.headline: Audit control aggregation app with streamlit
text.text: The application helps internal control managers to automate their control consolidation tasks and focus on exploiting the results. The application has made it possible to consolidate more than 500 controls (with their specific features) per month, and to carry out automatic e-mail reminders and anomaly reporting. The project is in line with the company's strong desire to digitize and automate all processes that are redundant and offer no added value for employees.

text.headline: Tree decisions with constraints app with Flask
text.text: Creation of a Flask application containing a configurable constraint tree (developed from scratch) for binary classification and ranking. The aim of the application is to speed up the modeling stage and provide a configurable tree that links business assumptions and tree splits for a high-performance model in line with business expertise.

text.headline: Auto Pricing
text.text: Creation of a Dash application enabling configurable portfolio pricings and cost forecasting, with different scenarios and simulations. The aim of the application is to automate pricing in just a few clicks, and gain greater reactivity during auctions.
